    <note>Zeng(1) Yi [1703] This may be a good example of the chain by which collateral kin and affines successively gain access to degree-holding and political careers. If, as seems probable, the Nancheng Zeng were related to the Nanfeng Zeng, then the latter rise to political prominence first, then the Nancheng Zeng, then the Linchuan Dong (who Hymes doesn't discuss) and their probable collateral kin, the Yongfeng Dong, who form a lineage that gets extensive coverage in Hymes. Jiangxi TZ, 21.16b; SHY:ZG, 43.2a-3a; Zeng Gong, WJ, 42.12b-135.</note>
